project/m4/synth/openlane_run.log
==================================

NOTE: This project used yowasp-yosys (a WebAssembly build of Yosys) rather
than OpenLane 2. The decision was documented in synth/m3/synthesis_notes.md
and again in synth/m4/synthesis_notes.md.

The actual synthesis logs are at:
  project/m4/synth/q15/yosys_run.log    (Q15 per-lane synthesis)
  project/m4/synth/int8/yosys_run.log   (INT8 per-lane synthesis)
  project/m4/synth/q4/yosys_run.log     (Q4 per-lane synthesis)

OpenLane was not available in the Windows + MSYS2 toolchain on the
development host; yowasp-yosys was selected as the synthesis tool because
it runs anywhere Python runs and uses the same sky130 standard cell PDK
that OpenLane would use. Synthesis numbers (area, cell count, critical
path depth) are directly comparable to OpenLane outputs because both tools
map to the same sky130_fd_sc_hd liberty file.

Static timing analysis used Yosys's `ltp` (longest topological path)
facility because OpenSTA is also not available in the yowasp toolchain.
The critical-path defensibility-by-analogy to M3 is documented in
project/m4/synth/synthesis_notes.md.

See also:
  project/m4/synth/q15/yosys_run.log     for the full Yosys log
  project/m4/synth/synthesis_notes.md    for methodology discussion
